column_.text_:
The sky's a shocking shade of despair. Guess we got Lilith
and Angra Mainyu to thank for that.

That pillar scares me more... Lilith called it the bridge to the
Astral Realm, right?

Only Angra Mainyu can open the gate. That pillar must be like
an altar for the rites.

Look at the very top! It's the light the gate came from. We
have to go investigate.

Stupid Lilith, goin' around, building creepy pillars in our
skies. She's gonna pay for this!

We have no choice but to fight. For our homes, for our loved
ones, for our world!

Did somebody say heebie-jeebies? Can't wait till I'm in a
tavern, drinking away this nightmare.

Grab a pen, Lilith. 'Cause I'm about to teach you the lesson of
a lifetime!

This is the last battle for real, right? 'Cause I am so ready for
a massage!

Lilith, your reign of terror ends today. We're going to save
Rolan. And the skies.

Geegee, Momo, be strong for just a little longer. We're
almost there!
Even if I have to lay down my life, I will stop Lilith!

All right, deep breaths, everybody! As long as we stick
together, there's nothing we can't do!

Compassion is ever warped by ambition... We must not
show Lilith mercy, for we shall receive none.

We can finally bring this conflict to an end. For the sake of
your homelands, push onward.

We've cornered that villain! By dawn tomorrow, peace will
reign over the skies once more!

I've gotta say, this pillar's almost as crooked as Lilith herself.
What say we go straighten her out, eh?
At long last, we have found the head of the snake...

Gahaha! Stars, gods, and an apocalypse. The Eternal Rage
Style shall crush aaall!

I'm all for dreaming big, Lilith, but when I find you, I'm going
to crush your sinister hopes!

The time has come... I will sever your ambitions at the root,
Lilith.

As much as I'd love to tear this pillar down piece by piece
and examine its interdimensional properties... Clock's
ticking.
Lilith... This ends today.
Let's go. We don't have much time.
You ready to get a move on? I'm worried about Fix It Dude.

Is it just me, or is the air real stuffy? Feels like I'm
suffocating.
Same... It's like this place is trying to force us out...
I can hear cries of sorrow and pain...
It's the trees and plants... Of Zegagrande...

Can you see all the wreckage scattered about? I believe
Lilith built this pillar out of people's homes...
What hole did this weirdo crawl out of?
It's part of Angra Mainyu.

Okay, so it's creepy and hostile. Least it'll be a good
warm-up before the final match!
Whoa! The hell was that?!
What? It doesn't feel like I'm cutting anything...
It's no use. I can't hit it!

The battle against Angra Mainyu was similar... It's like
fighting a shadow.

Reinforcements! Are those little ones also part of Angra
Mainyu?

Yes, but these actually have physical shape. I think our
attacks will work!

We're getting nowhere. Just focus on the small ones. Those
are the ones we can actually hit!

Uh... A weird portal just opened up. Think it's 'cause we
trounced all those Mini-Mainyus?

We're gonna need to hop into that suspicious portal, aren't
we?

It's the only chance we have at understanding Angra
Mainyu's powers.
Whoa!

We did go through that rift, right? It looks like we're still in
the same place, but everything's all hazy...

Look, the monster from before... Is it just me, or does it
appear solid now?

I bet it's because we went through that funky portal. I knew it
was a good idea!
Come on! We can finally fight that jerk! Let 'em have it!

Huh? Why'd you bring us back? We still need to beat that big
baddie!
Yeah! Not so tough now, are ya?!

I don't think we'll make it very far in this haze. Let's pass
through the rift again and return to the normal world.

Well, now that those spooky portal-monsters are gone, what
say we get a move on?

I can't believe they were residing in a different dimension...
It must have something to do with Angra Mainyu's powers as
gatekeeper.

I'm as shaken as you are... But at least we have a strategy
now.

Yes. Once you've figured out the key to its powers, no primal
beast is invincible.

Let's try not to linger in the other dimension though. If Angra
Mainyu closes off the portal, we may be cut off from this
world permanently.

I know you're probably shook by the whole interdimensional
travel thing, but we gotta go!
Come on, guys! We don't have time to be standing around.
Do you think Rolan's okay?

I can't say... There's still too much that we don't understand
about him and Lilith.

Man. Would it have killed Lilith to install a few hoists or
pulleys?
Don't get impatient. We need to be really, really careful.
Gah! How many spare parts does Angra Mainyu have?!

You all know the drill now! Wait for the Mini-Mainyu's to pop
up, then blast 'em!
Heads up crew! We've got spooky company!

Calm down, Rackam. They seem like normal monsters. They
must have been summoned here by Angra Mainyu.

The shadow-people just keep comin'! It's like something out
of a horror story!
Get! Lost! Ugh, they're so creepy!

Huh? Did you guys see that? The shadow-people just
disintegrated!

Yes... It must have been the light spilling from the rift. I
believe we've just found our key to victory.

Great... Fighting shadow-people in a shadow-world. Really
not where I wanted to be right now.

I don't think mortals were ever meant to step foot in this
realm... Let's try to stay by the portals, in the light.
Finally! I hope we never have to do that again!
Jeez... Shadow portals, shadow people... What's next?

Wait! I think I sense a primal beast... Or, at least something
that feels like a primal beast...
And this presence isn't Angra Mainyu?
No... It's... Huh? But that's impossible...

Lyria, we're hoppin' between dimensions at the drop of a hat.
Nothing's impossible.
Furycane? I thought we took care of you back at Tempeal!

We did. I absorbed Furycane, I know it... But this primal feels
exactly the same.

This Furycane looks even grumpier than the old one. Hope
you're ready for a storm!

I can't explain why, but I'm sure this isn't the Furycane we
faced before... Just who are you?

I know the voice of the wind. And you are singing a
completely different tune.

Hey, you big faker! You really shouldn't pretend to be
someone you're not!

I have no idea what's going on, but if you tell me what to
shoot, I'll shoot it!
I don't understand... If it's not a primal, then what is it?

This is your last chance. You can either settle down, or taste
my whip!

It just feels like an empty suit of armor... Without conviction,
this Furycane can never hope to prevail!

That is one freaky stallion-person. But your boy Vane's also
got unlimited horsepower!

The more the winds rage and howl, the brighter flares the
wildfire.

There is something strange at work... I can feel no will—no
life—from that creature.

It matters not what you are! Stand in the way of justice, and
my holy blade shall cut you down!

Can't say I've got any respect for phonies. What say I pare
you down 'til we get to your true form?

After the fiercest gales comes profound calm... This
tempest, like all others, will pass.

Let us see which possesses the greater force! My fists or
your typhoon!
I broke you once; I can easily break you again!

This aberration gives me the creeps. Let's make quick work
of it.

How do you have the powers of a primal without actually
being one? Don't bothering answering—I'll just crack you
open.
Out of my way.

I can't hear a voice... It's like this Furycane doesn't have any
thoughts at all...
There isn't a heart or mind... Just a shell...
It feels a lot like those shadow-people. Just... bigger.

And way more bloodthirsty! The old Furycane was a fart
compared to this tempest!

Ew! What's that coming out of those whirlwinds? Definitely
don't touch it!

This wind's about to bowl me over! Hey, Phony-Cane, if
you're not angry, what are you howling for?!
It's concentrating power... Watch out!
Phony-Pony is down. Get 'em!

The old mare's found her hooves again. And she doesn't look
happy!
O winds of vitality, bless us with life!
Heed my call... Furycane!
Aaaah!
Id!
We'll talk later. Revenge comes first.
Id... You saved my life!
Talk later.

I don't trust your hero act. After Furycane's dusted, I'm
gonna make you spill your evil master plan.
The wind's picking up... Get away from Furycane now!
Run, ruuun!

There's no guarding against this one. Get ready to dodge for
your lives!

Oh great, a magical girl transformation! I forgot Furycane
could do that.

Its attacks will become even more lethal. We can't afford any
slip-ups!
These damn winds! I can't move an inch!
Just hold on! They have to let up eventually!

Furycane's blows are gonna land a lot harder now. Try not to
get hit!
Now the party begins. Well, milady? Shall we dance?
Lyria, get someplace safe.
Okay!
Gaaah! It's sucking us in!

This is not how you treat a lady! Everyone, make a break
for it!

Furycane can't keep this up forever! Dig your heels in and
wait it out!
Oh no... Get ready for the vortex of doom!
Not today!
The heck?! He could stop that with just a slash?!
Commence counterattack.
I believe in you, everyone!
Now! Let it feel our thorns!
Back on its feet already?! Come on!
You're almost there, bud! I can feel it in my horns!
You're almost there, bud! I can feel it in my horns!
One last push.
We about ready to end this?! This pup's on its last legs!
Woo-hoo!
Is anyone hurt?

I feel like a million rupies. But, uh... What're we gonna do about
him?
Id, wait!
You want to stop Lilith too, don't you?

After all the time I spent with you, I know how much you care for
her.
But even if you love her, after what she's done, we have to stop her!
My mother...
Or Lilith, I should say, intends to sacrifice the future of this world.
I know I can't let her get away with that.
But I can no longer feign innocence. This has gone on long enough.
Wanna come with us then?
What do you say to a temporary truce?
What do you say to a temporary truce?
Wanna come with us then?
Wanna come with us then?
What do you say to a temporary truce?
What do you say to a temporary truce?

You wanna stop her and so do we. Choices don't get any
easier than that!
How 'bout it? We could use ya!

Why? Considering the scale of violence I inflicted on your
crew...
Well... In the end, you did help us.
A past enemy is a future friend. That's what they say!
All right. I'll join you in the fight against Lilith.
Let's stop her.
Welcome to the winning team, Id!
Yeah.
You're not much of a people person, are you?
Sorry.
Haha...
Pal! Where you think you're going?
About-face! We don't have time for games!
Hey, sillyhead! That's where we came from!
We should go. There's not much time to spare.
Come on, kid. We got a date with Lilith to keep.
Hey, Id... Lilith's your mom, right?
Adoptive. We're not related by blood, but I owe her my life.
If you want to turn back, no one will blame you.
I've made my choice.

You might say that now. But when she's right there in front
of you... It's gonna be tough.

I'd rather face her myself than have her suffer at someone
else's hands.

As family, you must feel responsible for her crimes... Very
well. We'll respect your wishes.
Um... Id?
What is it?

I wanted to thank you. For protecting me while I was
imprisoned by the Church of Avia.
You're... thanking me? I was the one who captured you.

Yes, that's true... But you also helped bring me back to my
friends.

If you'd left me with Lilith, who knows what would have
happened to me....
Yeah, I guess...
I think I'm having déjà vu!

Id. Those monsters share a body and powers with Angra
Mainyu. Defeat the small ones first.
Understood.
What? Just how many of these shadows are there?

You can't vanquish the shadows with brute force! Just push
your way through for now!
Finally! Adios, losers!

Id, there's something I wanted to ask you about. Last time
we crossed swords, you transformed...

Oh yeah! What was that? If you ask me, I thought you looked
like a giant lizard.

Well, you're wrong. That was a manifestation of the dragon
powers sleeping within me.

Lilith trained me when I was young, taught me how to
control them. I thought I'd be saving the world with them,
but...

You will be, kid. That's the whole reason you joined us on this
crazy mission, right?

The near infinite power of dragons is a heavy burden to bear.
But you aren't alone.
So you also...? These skies are stranger than I thought...

I get it now... The Furycane we just fought? It was like a
shadow, made from our memory of the real thing.

So not only was it a counterfeit primal, it never truly existed
at all... Correct?

Yes. I think it's because time and space is so unstable
here—reality's getting all mixed up...

But who ever heard of a shadow with the destructive force of
a primal? Vayoi truly is fearsome...
Pretending to be the wolf of Leautagne?
It's even tougher than the real Managarmr. Be careful!

Looks like dog-breath is as fast as ever! Keep a close eye on
its paw-work!

We now know these shadow-primals are not invincible.
There's nothing to be afraid of!

We already beat OG Managarmr, right? This fight's in the
bag!

I'm gonna need time for my incantations... Can I get some
protection?
I'd be pissed too if I was being kept on a leash.

My heart goes out to this child... What do you think it's like
to not fully exist?

I can't imagine how empty you must feel... I wish we could
do more than put you to sleep.
Let's see whose frost is deadlier.

Speed isn't exactly my specialty, but it's cool! I always did
like a good game of whack-a-wolf!

Ice armor? I am the Lord of Flames. You might as well seek
to parry steel with silk.

Managarmr moves in quick bursts, but he's still unable to
change direction. Predict his path and we've won the day.

We've already defeated a shade in the form of Furycane. The
same tactics should work on this beast!

Wretched thing... Having to abide without a soul, that's a fate
worse than death, it is...

Never have I met a creature so far outside the natural order...
I can only hope you find peace in eternal rest.

No matter how the blizzard blows and blusters... It can't
control the heat of my raaage!

What is this, another dead ringer? Someone's getting
desperate.

You've already done enough. Let me guide you to the other
side.

So you're a being of immense power zapped outta nothing.
That's breaking a few laws of alchemy. I'll need to extract a
heavy fine.
Get lost.
Whoa! What's with the boom-fest?!

It's the purple icicles. They explode upon impact! Steer clear
of the blast!
Jeez. Can't a guy get some rest on a battlefield?!
It's down! Get cruisin' and give it a bruisin'!
Perfect. Now it's our turn to lead this dance!
It's back up! Watch out for counterattacks!

Looks like Wolfie's about to start leaping again! Stay on your
toes, you guys!
The hell is this? Some kind of mating dance?
Ugh... Is everyone all right?!
It's got us pinned down. We have to do something!
Yeah, I know! But what?!
I recognize that spear...
Muahaha! No one goes hunting without the Silver Wolf!
I... can't feel my face...
Now this is my kind of party...
Got room for one more guest?
Huh?! What are you doing here?!

Heard you got some big prey lined up! Well, I got room on my
wall for a few more trophies!
He's... not talking about mounting our heads, is he?

I hope not. I'd much rather have Gallanza as an ally than a
foe.
Muahahaha! No autographs 'til after the fight!
Yeah... I'll take the help. But hard pass on the autographs.
Arooo! Lemme hear your battle howls!
Damn, I think Gallanza's got this on his own!
Hey, Gallanza. I appreciate it.
Blegh, sentiment. I hate it! I'm just here for the thrill!
Of course.
Bark all you want! You don't scare me, you overgrown puppy!
On your guard! It's going to strike hard and strike fast!
This fight would go a lot smoother if you would just sit!
It's so fast... Look out!
It's huge... I guess grappling is no longer an option.
It's coming for us. Watch out for its ranged attacks!

Yes... Yes! A death match with a god! Now that's what I call
raging hot!

Man, I wish I had your kind of energy! You should really bottle
that stuff.
Careful! It's charging for an attack!

What the? Ice confetti? Does this mean the party's finally
getting started?
Today's weather forecast... Deadly with a chance of icicles!

The icicles have homing capabilities. If you can't evade them,
destroy them!
Incoming! Get ready to dodge!
Dodging is for puppies! Attacking is for wolves!
Smart.
Now I know where Id gets his violent streak from...
Ah, the smell of fresh blood in the snow... Time for the kill!
Huh?
Go on ahead. Let me... catch my breath...
Wait... You're gonna sleep here?
We owe you, Gallanza.

We're about halfway there, right? My wings are getting
sore...

I know you're all tired, but we haven't reached out goal yet.
Stay strong.
My prey... never escapes...
I'm proud of you... Id...
This silence is unnatural...

Id, I've always wondered... When you were part of the
Church, why did you go to such lengths to protect Lyria?

I was only following orders, at least at first. Lyria was the key
to bringing salvation.

But then you learned all Lilith wanted to save was herself.
Lyria was no more than a means to an end.

Once she had made Lyria absorb enough primals, Lilith
meant to free Angra Mainyu and sacrifice all who opposed
her.

I gave myself to Mother's cause. I trained and trained to
protect her vision of salvation.

When I learned it was all a lie, my life was devoid of meaning.
There was nothing I wanted to fight for anymore.

Except Lyria. Now, I'm protecting her because it's the first
thing my heart's ever told me to do.
For the love of—what is it this time?!
Looks like weird icky stuff is comin' to swallow us!

Yeah, I don’t like the look of that... Who knows what'll
happen if we touch it!
I sense something... It's the primal beast from Phondam.

Please tell me that's a bad joke. We don't have any real
estate to fight on!
No! We've reached a dead end!
That was close...
You're welcome, by the way.
Huh? Aren't you...
But I suppose etiquette can wait.
First, a dance!
Maglielle, right? What made you decide to switch teams?

Not that I don't appreciate the help but... I've had my fill of
bloodlusty carnivores.

Why, I never! Would you kindly refrain from comparing me to
General Gallanza?
I am here as a matter of pride.

If word got out that the vanquishers of my dear fellowship
suffocated in a bog, I'd never hear the end of it!
Finally, it stopped flailing. Now get in there!
The stage is ours. Remember, everyone! With grace!
It's recovered... Get ready for counterattacks!
It's back up and looking angrier than before!
You dance well... For a loathsome charlatan.

We're wearing it down! Everyone, just stay calm and keep
slingin'!
You're almost there, everyone!
My, my. Looks like the tempo's about to pick up.
Uh-oh! We made it mad. Watch out!
Damn... Get away from the snake!

It's going for our footholds! Other than the miniature dragon,
I don't suppose any of you can fly.
Oh no. Run!
I don't think so!
Yeah, Twinkle Toes! Nice moves!
Haah!
Now, the show can go on!
And this is why you never mess with Maggie.
Uh-huh... Think I'd rather tango with death.
Fireball! I forgot about the fireball!
If we don't put out that fire, we're toast. Literally!
See where the mana's flowing from? Aim for those parts!
The magma's rising! Don't burn your toes!

That was stupendous. Now the stage is set for our grand
finale!
This is not good for my blood pressure...
Look! It's conjuring up another fire ball!
Give it up, scaley! That trick's not gonna work on us!

Dear me. The magma-level's risen. Do watch your step,
everyone!
You did it! The fire ball disappeared!
Look upon my star-shattering blade!
Behold the ancient art of my clan!
Now... Feast your eyes!

I wasn't in a position to admire your swordplay before, but
let me say now: your skill with magic blades is unparalleled.

That's quite flattering—especially because you've only seen
the opening act.

The Sword Veil allied itself with Avia to bring salvation to the
skies... Now at last, we can rise to the occasion!
Hey, Maggie... Thanks.

Oh my. It's been a while since you've called me by that name.
Have you by any chance grown soft?
I could ask the same of you.
Pleasant dreams.
Make no mistake, skyfarers.

This was merely a matter of honor. Do not disgrace
yourselves by thanking me.
And so, I bid you adieu.

Phew... I can't believe we're still breathing. If Maglielle
hadn't come, we'd probably be smores by now.
It's too soon to celebrate. Come on.
Let's get a move on already. It's creepy in here.
We should go. Angra Mainyu's close... I can feel it.
Ceiling's gotten higher. Should mean we're almost at the top.
The more I see that sky, the more I hate it.
Yeah. Lilith's got some messed-up taste.
Let's keep moving, bud. I'm getting claustrophobic.

Let's move on. We can't turn back now, even if we wanted
to.
This should be the last battle. Make sure you're prepared.
Hey... You seeing what I'm seeing?

Is that the gate to the Astral Realm? It looks even scarier up
close...

Strange, isn't it? Gateways are usually a symbol of hope and
new opportunity...

Not this one. Like Rolan said, if that door opens, then the
skies will fall.
We won't let it open.
Yep. We'll beat Lilith, grab Rolan, then skedaddle outta here.
Sounds like a plan!

Had you only seen things my way, this pitiful fate could have
been avoided.

Why must you insist on quarreling with your own brethren?
It's unfathomable, truly...
Rolan, no!
Ah, shaman. Impeccable timing as always, I see.
Can you feel the grip of imminent salvation?
I invite you and your other half to watch.
And, Id... Is this betrayal?
Where did I go wrong?

You can't sacrifice our skies to open that gate! We won't let
you do it!

This is our home... And it means more to us than you'll ever
know!

Blowin' up the world to help yourself? Just how selfish can
you be?
Once I reach Estalucia, I shall guide this world to utopia.
Why would anyone reject my heartfelt invitation?
Aah... How I pity you poor, misguided creatures.
Yeah, like we give a crap about anything you say.

Your messed up utopia is built on sacrifice; no way we're
lettin' that fly.
Options fail me. I can no longer sway your hearts or minds.
As a parting gift...
May you all find solace in death's warm embrace.

Heads up, you big dumb bully! It's only called "salvation"
when you're actually saving people!

You're only fighting for yourself, but we're fighting for all
skydwellers. That's why we'll prevail!

So we're finally at the top... Let's make sure we're the last
ones standing!

If there's one thing I can't stand, it's selfish people! I'm so not
losing to you!

Hah! We'll kick your ass so hard, you won't need a portal to
sail to the stars!

Will you never understand? It's not your place to determine
how others live or die!

Stop with the word games. You aren't offering peace in
death; you're threatening murder!

Your tyranny ends today! I swear it on the honor of the White
Dragons!

If you read your hero books, you'd definitely know good
always triumphs over evil!

A true leader does not ask their people to die for them, but
rather, is willing to die for their people.

You're prepared, then, to lay aside both life and morality for
ambition. So be it.

Look around at the beautiful skies you seek to destroy! Do
you feel no pain? No remorse?!

Conviction is power. Don't matter whether it's good or evil.
But you can bet your last coin we're just as determined as
you are!

You have brought no beauty into this world... When you die,
so will your legacy!
May the most righteous fists win! Haaaaah!

Excuse me? Solace in death? You can take your solace and
shove it!

The skies will live to see tomorrow, but the same can't be
said of your corrupt ambition.

Astrals sure are twisted, huh? Lemme send you to an
asylum, AKA the dimensional rift!
This is how is has to be!
Id. Please don't disappoint me any further.

You can still redeem yourself. Eradicate these nuisances and
come back to Mother...
No! Please, listen to me—

I think you've lost sight of the big picture. What's a few
skydoms when compared to all of eternity?
If I can just absorb Angra Mainyu...

I'm afraid that's impossible. Angra Mainyu is completely
under my command.

It seems I'm a bit short on power. Astraeus, be a dear, won't
you?
Gah... Aah... Agh!
Damn! Hang in there, Rolan! We're gonna save you!
It's no use! Feels like we're fighting a mirage!
Real body... Through the gate...

Of course! How could we have forgotten? Angra Mainyu must
be in another dimension.

The real Angra Mainyu isn't here! We need to switch
dimensions!

It's the mini-Mainyus! If we beat these suckers, we can open
up a portal!

Come on! Let's crush these rocks and do some 
dimension-hopping!
Hey! Keep your grubby paws off our crewmate!

If those hands can grab us, that should mean we can hit
back!
Angra Grab-Yu's got someone again. Help 'em out!

That glow... Could it be from all the friction? An unanticipated
annoyance.
Guys? The paws aren't moving anymore.

They went still as soon as the portal's light hit them. We can
use that to our advantage.
Look! It stopped moving again!

Angra Mainyu's weak to light! Are all evil gods this
predictable?

Angra Mainyu's begun amassing huge amounts of energy!
We need to find a way to stop it!

Why struggle? The sooner you accept death's embrace, the
sooner you can be at peace.

Mother, please! You have to understand! This isn't
salvation—it's destruction!
Angra Mainyu's getting weaker! You're almost there!
Am I... losing? How? This is impossible...
Skydwellers... You ignorant, stubborn swine...
Now! Begin the counter-assault!

Stop resisting... You're mortals. You're all going to die
eventually!
Stay on your guard! One wrong move, and it's all over!

You non-believers... For your hubris, taste now of
retribution!

I offered you a chance to repent. It was you that elected to
suffer!

Angra Mainyu is focusing its power! You have to find some
way to stop it!
What the hell?! How are we supposed to dodge?!
Filthy interlopers... Death would be a mercy to you.

I'll send you hurtling into a bottomless abyss, where you'll
writhe for all eternity.
We took down one of its dirty paws!
I think we weakened its main body too!
All right! We got another hand!
Hah! That's what you deserve for... getting out of hand.
Guess we have the upper hand now!
Now I need to restore Angra Mainyu. Lovely... Just lovely.
The main body's down! Time to unleash heck!
Oh no! Fix-it Dude!
Where do you miniscule skydwellers find such power?
Hey, look! The gateway's closing!
I'm sorry to preclude celebrations but...
We're not done yet!
